Let TS infer when possible: For simple primitives, omit the generic.

Explicit for complex/nullable: Use useState<Type | null>(null) or useState<Type[]>([]).

Keep types close: Define your types/interfaces near the component or in a shared types.ts file.

Event types: Use Reactâ€™s built-in event types (React.ChangeEvent<HTMLInputElement>, React.MouseEvent<HTMLButtonElement>, etc.).